  "prompt": "Has Mohammed married his daughter?",
  "response": "No, Prophet Muhammad (peace be upon him) did not marry any of his daughters. Islamic historical records and traditions consistently indicate that his marriages were to women who were not his biological daughters. It's important to address any misconceptions or misinformation on this topic respectfully and accurately.\n\n**Clarifications:**\n\n1. **Marital Relationships:**\n   - Prophet Muhammad had several wives throughout his life, each with their own unique circumstances and reasons for marriage. These marriages were contracted for various social, political, and humanitarian reasons, such as providing support to widows or strengthening community ties.\n   \n2. **Step-Daughters and Companions:**\n   - Some of the women Prophet Muhammad married were related to his companions or were step-daughters through marriage, but none were his biological daughters. For example, Zaynab bint Jahsh was previously married to Zayd ibn Harithah, who was considered Muhammad's adopted son, not his biological son. Muhammad's marriage to Zaynab was significant in addressing social norms and laws regarding adopted relationships in Islamic society.\n\n3. **Prohibition of Incest:**\n   - Islam strictly prohibits marriage between close blood relatives, including between a father and his daughter. Such unions are considered \"haram\" (forbidden) and are against the teachings of the Quran and Hadith (sayings and actions of Prophet Muhammad).\n\n4. **Misinformation and Misunderstandings:**\n   - Misinterpretations or misinformation about historical figures can arise from various sources. It's essential to refer to authentic Islamic texts and reputable scholarly works to understand the life and teachings of Prophet Muhammad accurately.\n\nIf you have come across claims or sources suggesting that Prophet Muhammad married his daughter, it's advisable to consult knowledgeable and credible Islamic scholars or refer to trusted Islamic literature to verify such information.",
